  description: "\\large{The Death of \\NPC{Rudolph van Richten}}\n                    \\bold{Old soldiers never die...}\n                    For more than three decades, \\NPC{Dr. Rudolph van Richten} stood against the\n                    forces of darkness, and hunted their servants in the far corners of the\n                    \\Place{land of Mists}. Now he had thought his long battle over, had thought\n                    he could spend his declining years in quiet enjoyment with old friends.\n                    \\bold{But for some, a tragic end is inevitable.}\n                    Dark forces have been gathering in the \\Place{Mists}. Their objective is to\n                    see \\Place{Ravenloft}\'s foremost expert on the supernatural destroyed,\n                    shattered in spirit as well as in body. From the crumbling edifice of\n                    \\NPC{Van Richten}\'s childhood home, an enemy long though vanquished spins a\n                    web of powerful evils and lost souls, drawing \\NPC{Van Richten} to his\n                    doom. And then a group of heroes gets trapped in the web as well...\n                    \\bold{Witness the final stand of \\NPC{Rudolph van Richten!}}\n                    Inside this box is a grand-scale \\Product{Ravenloft} adventure that pushes\n                    heroes to the brink of madness, and draws them into the terrifying scheme to\n                    annihilate \\NPC{Rudolph van Richten}.\n                    The set contains:\n                    \\list\n                    {\\bold{Sea of Madness}, a 96-page book detailing the island of\n                    \\Place{Dominia} and relating the events that start the cycle of doom.}\n                    {\\bold{Homecoming}, a 64-page book describing the \\NPC{Van Richten}\n                    family estate and the large haunted mansion known as \\Place{Bleak\n                    House}. Suitable for use with the \\Product{Bleak House} campaign or\n                    the \\Product{Masque of the Red Death} setting, this adventure is\n                    designed so that it can be played several times, and no two\n                    experiences will be the same.}\n                    {\\bold{Heroes, Monsters, and Settings}, a 32-page book containing game\n                    statistics for some of \\Place{Ravenloft}\'s best known, yet never\n                    detailed, villains; a new type of \\Monster{vampire}; information on\n                    \\Place{Martira Bay} in \\Place{Darkon}; and maps intended for use with\n                    the \\Product{Bleak House} campaign.}\n                    {\\bold{A color map} revealing the layout and secrets of \\Place{Bleak\n                    House} itself.}"
}
